        }
      },
      {
        "id": "d7-vze1mXWrP_9r9",
        "title": "Text 23",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary based on students’ experiences. Students can verify their predictions after doing the experiment.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "U0NcQl4aYbw8xeci",
        "title": "Text 25",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><u>Conduct an Experiment</u></p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "U75r7GWKZxbZBkI8",
        "title": "Text 26",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><em>Equipment</em></p><ul><li>Two coins</li><li>A way to record results, such as paper, pencil, etc.</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "ZzFu3FA0ghP2HpGg",
        "title": "Text 27",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><em>Directions (individually, with a partner, or small group)</em></p><ul><li>Toss two coins 30 times</li><li>Keep track of the number of times the coins match and the number of times the coins do not match</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "qYZi1OOCVAKwqekB",
        "title": "Text 29",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Results will vary based on data collection and randomness. </p><p>There should be close to 15 matches and 15 no-matches.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "V69lOOuIj95-70dE",
        "title": "Text 31",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><u>Analyze the Data</u></p><ul><li>Based on your data, write a ratio for the experimental probability of getting a match? Of getting a no match?</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "WOB7kgysP-qtsQLS",
        "title": "Text 33",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Results will vary based on data collection and randomness.</p><p>Example answer:</p><p>P(match) = 13/30 </p><p>P(no match) = 17/30</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "wY9N27I_HnNBAzJm",
        "title": "Text 35",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Combine your data with your classmates and find the experimental probabilities. Based on this data, would your prediction about the probability of a match or no-match change? Explain.</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "63ppmJHUeRBWTNuR",
        "title": "Text 37",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary. Some students will already have the P(match) = 15/30.</p><p>The class data should support a probability close to 50% for each. It would be surprising to have a set of class data with a match percent outside the 45% to 55% range.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "rgAHHbZgkuRmHppg",
        "title": "Text 39",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>If you toss the two coins 100 times, how many times would expect a match to occur? A no match to occur? Explain.</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "-lxTDisR6Cjx9f92",
        "title": "Text 41",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Example answer:</p><p>Matches seem to happen 50% of the time. So, in 100 trials, we would get 50 matches.</p><p>P(match) = 15/30 = 50/100</p>"
          ]
        }
      }
